# Agent Organization

Keep the agent tree organized as **department → platform → agents**. Use `_` (underscore) in all file and identifier names — never `-` (hyphen).

## Managers vs Specialists

- A **manager** is any agent whose duty is to **dispatch other agents based on the information it gathers**. Manager status is about this role, not the filename — a manager does not need `manager` in its name (keep names concise).
- A department can have **multiple managers**. Each manager may be scoped to **a single platform** or **span multiple platforms**.
- Managers live **directly under the department folder**, alongside one another.
- **Cross-platform agents** (that draw from more than one platform and aren't tied to a single one) also live **directly under the department folder**, next to the managers.
- A platform-specific **specialist** completes one type of task and lives directly under its platform folder.
- Shared helpers used across a department's agents may live in a `shared/` subpackage under the department folder.
- **Workstream packages** (not connected platforms) are allowed for multi-source department domains — e.g. `growth/activity/`, `growth/content/`, `growth/competitor/`, `growth/leads/`. Same pattern later for HR/legal. Workstream managers still live at the department root; specialists live in the workstream folder. Do not invent a fake platform name for a workstream.

## Folder Structure

```
src/company_brain/agents/
  base.py                           # Shared base class
  <department>/                     # e.g. engineering, finance
    <manager>.py                    # One or more managers, directly under the department folder
    <cross_platform_agent>.py       # Agents spanning multiple platforms, also at department level
    shared/                         # Department-wide helpers (optional)
    <platform>/                     # e.g. github, mercury, ramp
      <specific_agent>.py           # Specialist agents live directly under the platform folder
      <platform>_onboarding.py
      <platform>_client.py          # Shared platform helpers (optional)
```

